This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new objective for policy optimization that can be directly estimated from samples. It also uses proximal policy optimization techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with policy learning and control. The system (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant as it involves control and optimization. Finally, the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category may be relevant as the proposed algorithm is evaluated on continuous control benchmarks.
